9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 353, L.D. 534, “An Act to Clarify the
10 Rights of Crime Victims and Witnesses Regarding Professional Investigator
11 Communications”
12 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
13 following:
14 'Sec. 1. 17-A MRSA §2110 is enacted to read:
15 §2110. Victim and witness rights when contacted by professional investigator
16 The duties of a professional investigator, as defined in Title 32, section 8103,
17 subsection 5, when contacting a victim or witness of a crime, are set out in rules adopted
18 by the Chief of the State Police pursuant to Title 32, section 8116, subsection 3, including
19 the disclosure of the right of a victim or witness to refuse communication.
20 Sec. 2. 32 MRSA §8103, sub-§1-D is enacted to read:
21 1-D. Crime. "Crime" has the same meaning as in Title 17-A, section 2101, subsection
22 1.
23 Sec. 3. 32 MRSA §8103, sub-§6 is enacted to read:
24 6. Victim. "Victim" has the same meaning as in Title 17-A, section 2101, subsection
25 2.
26 Sec. 4. 32 MRSA §8103, sub-§7 is enacted to read:
27 7. Witness. "Witness" has the same meaning as in Title 15, section 1412, subsection
28 3.
29 Sec. 5. 32 MRSA §8104, sub-§2, ¶A, as amended by PL 2011, c. 366, §18, is
30 further amended to read:
31 A. A person employed by or on behalf of the Federal Government, any state or any
32 political subdivision or public instrumentality or a Canadian province, while in the
